@startuml
title Live Streaming and Camera Control

actor Operator
participant Browser
participant "Control Plane API" as API
participant "Stream Orchestrator" as Orchestrator
participant "Stream Gateway" as Gateway
participant Reconstructor
participant "Device Control Service" as Control
participant "ONVIF Camera" as Camera

Operator -> Browser: Open dashboard tile
Browser -> API: Request live session capabilities
API -> Orchestrator: resolve stream policy
Orchestrator -> Gateway: create or reuse session(cameraId, policy)

alt Direct session is enough
  Gateway -> Camera: Read selected source
else New stream needed
  Gateway -> Reconstructor: Ensure enhanced or fused pipeline
  Reconstructor -> Camera: Read main and companion RTSP sources
  Reconstructor --> Gateway: Processed stream feed
end

Gateway --> Orchestrator: session ready
Orchestrator --> API: session descriptor
API --> Browser: preferred transport + fallback transport
Browser -> Gateway: Connect to live session
Gateway --> Browser: Video stream
Browser --> Operator: Render live view

opt PTZ or auxiliary control
  Operator -> Browser: Move / snapshot / toggle light
  Browser -> API: Device control request
  API -> Control: execute command
  Control -> Camera: ONVIF PTZ / snapshot / auxiliary command
  Camera --> Control: Result
  Control --> API: command outcome
  API --> Browser: Success or error
end

Browser -> Gateway: Disconnect
Gateway -> Orchestrator: update session metrics
Orchestrator -> Gateway: apply idle or keep-warm policy

@enduml
